[chuckles]

257
00:19:14,383 --> 00:19:16,719
Why'd you go quiet?

258
00:19:16,785 --> 00:19:19,488
I'm curious
why the journal fell down.

259
00:19:19,555 --> 00:19:22,124
Because it was hanging off
the ledge.

260
00:19:22,192 --> 00:19:25,161
Things fall, gravity.

261
00:19:25,228 --> 00:19:27,129
What if it were the ghost?

262
00:19:27,197 --> 00:19:29,165
The smelly ghost was my dog.

263
00:19:29,232 --> 00:19:31,467
You know I'm talking
about the real ghost.

264
00:19:31,533 --> 00:19:33,102
There was no real ghost.

265
00:19:33,169 --> 00:19:34,170
Yes, there was.

266
00:19:34,237 --> 00:19:35,804
No, there wasn't.

267
00:19:35,871 --> 00:19:37,640
What about the photo?

268
00:19:37,706 --> 00:19:39,875
It's here somewhere.

269
00:19:39,942 --> 00:19:41,911
[suspenseful music]

270
00:19:53,022 --> 00:19:54,391
I don't want to see it.

271
00:19:57,193 --> 00:19:58,161
Come on.

272
00:19:58,228 --> 00:19:59,762
We'll be late for the lawyer.

273
00:20:06,902 --> 00:20:08,904
[jazzy music]

274
00:20:25,621 --> 00:20:27,223
[Amber] Here we are.

275
00:20:27,290 --> 00:20:28,524
There is a chair right here.
I'm going to help guide you.

276
00:20:28,590 --> 00:20:31,026
Lily, you are more beautiful
than ever.

277
00:20:31,093 --> 00:20:32,195
[Lily] Only on the outside.

278
00:20:32,262 --> 00:20:33,996
[chuckles] I beg to differ.

279
00:20:34,063 --> 00:20:36,865
You are a lovely soul.

280
00:20:37,933 --> 00:20:40,102
Not anymore.

281
00:20:40,170 --> 00:20:43,005
Oh, leaving your frame
of mind to the doctors.

282
00:20:43,072 --> 00:20:48,278
I will provide you with the one
thing I am insanely proficient at,

283
00:20:49,578 --> 00:20:51,113
legal jump rope.

284
00:20:53,082 --> 00:20:57,253
The... the cops haven't found out
who hit me and run yet.

285
00:20:57,320 --> 00:20:59,255
So why do I need to be here?

286
00:20:59,322 --> 00:21:00,723
Being that you survived,

287
00:21:00,789 --> 00:21:04,526
that leaves you still
as the sole beneficiary.

288
00:21:04,593 --> 00:21:08,231
[Amber] Meaning she still
inherits the $500 million?

289
00:21:08,298 --> 00:21:11,533
Minus legal fees, yeah.

290
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:17,240
So, what are you going to do
with your fortune, Lily?

291
00:21:17,307 --> 00:21:18,974
I don't know.

292
00:21:19,041 --> 00:21:21,910
Well, I'm sure
you'll figure it out.

293
00:21:21,977 --> 00:21:24,513
[grunts] Uh, young lady,

294
00:21:25,315 --> 00:21:26,582
young lady,

295
00:21:26,648 --> 00:21:28,984
would you please hand these
to Lily?

296
00:21:30,552 --> 00:21:33,490
Oh, and here's a pen.

297
00:21:38,495 --> 00:21:40,430
Miss Vegas.

298
00:21:40,497 --> 00:21:44,267
Miss Vegas will act as witness
to the legal signing

299
00:21:44,334 --> 00:21:49,472
of the transference
of monies from the trustees

300
00:21:49,538 --> 00:21:52,442
to her personal account.

301
00:21:52,509 --> 00:21:54,943
- [upbeat music]
- [record scratch]

302
00:21:55,010 --> 00:21:56,045
Young lady?

303
00:21:57,347 --> 00:21:59,349
- Amber.
- Amber, um,

304
00:21:59,416 --> 00:22:04,487
could you please confirm
that all is proper and true

305
00:22:04,553 --> 00:22:09,658
to which Lily is signing,
being that she has no reference of sight?

306
00:22:09,725 --> 00:22:12,628
- [upbeat music]
- [Amber clears her throat]

307
00:22:12,694 --> 00:22:14,630
[lawyer clears his throat]

308
00:22:14,696 --> 00:22:18,134
"I, Lily Chevalier, being of sound
mind on this day, July 20th..."

309
00:22:18,201 --> 00:22:22,938
- And so on and blah, blah, blah, blah, blah.
- [Amber continues reading]

310
00:22:23,005 --> 00:22:27,310
God created the universe
in seven days

311
00:22:27,377 --> 00:22:30,213
and it's taking you longer
to read two lines.

312
00:22:32,047 --> 00:22:33,982
It's all standard boilerplate.

313
00:22:34,049 --> 00:22:36,152
Just sign.

314
00:22:37,387 --> 00:22:38,620
Ah, women.

315
00:22:40,022 --> 00:22:41,357
Here,

316
00:22:41,424 --> 00:22:44,059
you're about to be
filthy fucking rich, girl.

317
00:22:44,126 --> 00:22:45,994
- Mm-hmm.
- Anything else?

318
00:22:46,061 --> 00:22:48,664
Ah. Thank you, dear.

319
00:22:48,730 --> 00:22:52,235
It'll take one week for the
transaction to be completed.

320
00:22:52,302 --> 00:22:54,504
Why so fucking long?

321
00:22:54,571 --> 00:22:57,173
Red tape bureaucracy.

322
00:22:57,240 --> 00:22:58,841
If you want to change the law,

323
00:22:58,907 --> 00:23:00,343
become a congresswoman.

324
00:23:01,610 --> 00:23:03,179
- [kisses]
- [sighs]

325
00:23:03,246 --> 00:23:04,813
[Amber] Come on, let's go, Lily.

326
00:23:11,887 --> 00:23:14,524
Oh, young lady,
can you please close the door?

327
00:23:16,493 --> 00:23:18,093
Can you close the door, please?

328
00:23:25,168 --> 00:23:28,505
You definitely cheated
on the bar exam

329
00:23:28,571 --> 00:23:32,375
because there's no way
a slimy turd like you

330
00:23:32,442 --> 00:23:35,545
who can't even get off your fat ass
to handle your client legal papers

331
00:23:35,612 --> 00:23:38,881
could possibly have the energy
to walk to class,

332
00:23:38,947 --> 00:23:40,949
let alone walk the talk.

333
00:23:49,958 --> 00:23:51,126
Hmmm.

334
00:23:53,996 --> 00:23:55,731
Sure.

335
00:23:55,797 --> 00:23:57,467
Blind sign it, Lily.

336
00:23:58,601 --> 00:24:01,803
I'd have someone watch over her

337
00:24:03,105 --> 00:24:06,875
to make sure I get my money.

338
00:24:06,942 --> 00:24:08,877
One, two,

339
00:24:08,944 --> 00:24:11,680
three, four, five, six, seven...

340
00:24:12,482 --> 00:24:13,815
[loud knocking]

341
00:24:37,005 --> 00:24:39,242
Amber, Lily with you?

342
00:24:39,309 --> 00:24:41,109
[Amber] <i>No.</i>

343
00:24:41,177 --> 00:24:42,378
She's not answering.

344
00:24:43,479 --> 00:24:44,447
I'll be right over.

345
00:24:44,514 --> 00:24:45,548
Okay.

346
00:24:46,649 --> 00:24:49,285
- [eerie music]
- [sighs]

347
00:25:00,996 --> 00:25:03,899
[chuckles] How do you think
I make my living?

348
00:25:05,235 --> 00:25:06,835
Hold this.

349
00:25:06,902 --> 00:25:08,770
Thank you.

350
00:25:08,837 --> 00:25:11,073
Oh, yes, almost there.

351
00:25:17,879 --> 00:25:20,283
Well, at least no dead body.

352
00:25:20,350 --> 00:25:21,384
Please.

353
00:25:22,352 --> 00:25:23,553
I wonder where.

354
00:25:25,622 --> 00:25:26,755
I might have an idea.

355
00:25:27,557 --> 00:25:28,625
Come on.

356
00:25:28,691 --> 00:25:30,426
[suspenseful music]

357
00:25:39,535 --> 00:25:40,769
[Lily] You picked the lock.

358
00:25:42,272 --> 00:25:44,873
How could you know that?

359
00:25:44,940 --> 00:25:48,311
My senses beyond sight
are becoming more sensitive.

360
00:25:49,746 --> 00:25:51,046
I heard of that happening,

361
00:25:51,113 --> 00:25:53,650
but how could you know
about the lock?

362
00:25:53,716 --> 00:25:57,587
Also, you couldn't be here unless
you checked the house first.

363
00:25:57,654 --> 00:25:59,222
[Amber] We could have found
a spare.

364
00:25:59,289 --> 00:26:02,024
No, I don't have one.

365
00:26:02,090 --> 00:26:04,926
You ever think about opening
your own detective agency?

366
00:26:06,496 --> 00:26:07,796
Someone's watching.

367
00:26:08,930 --> 00:26:10,932
Been there before you came.

368
00:26:10,999 --> 00:26:13,436
I'm going to pay that no good son
of a bitch a drunken sailor's visit.

369
00:26:13,503 --> 00:26:16,372
Don't.
It could be dangerous.

370
00:26:16,439 --> 00:26:18,308
Someone wants me dead remember?

371
00:26:24,447 --> 00:26:25,682
Who?

372
00:26:25,748 --> 00:26:28,950
I'm not that good
of a detective yet.

373
00:26:31,554 --> 00:26:33,889
- Let's go.
- Yes, let's go.

374
00:26:50,807 --> 00:26:52,642
[cane tapping]

375
00:26:57,447 --> 00:27:02,251
Hey, Lily, hold up.
You've been practicing.

376
00:27:02,318 --> 00:27:04,487
- Are we being followed?
- Yep.

377
00:27:04,554 --> 00:27:07,022
How do you know?
Eyes behind your head?

378
00:27:08,123 --> 00:27:09,492
Eyes in front of my head.

379
00:27:19,968 --> 00:27:21,337
[doctor] Look to the right,
please.

380
00:27:22,338 --> 00:27:25,941
Blind as a bat.

381
00:27:26,007 --> 00:27:28,745
Oh, sorry, by the way.

382
00:27:28,811 --> 00:27:34,450
Unfortunately, the optics, sclera,
retina, fovea, macula, and optic nerve

383
00:27:34,517 --> 00:27:36,017
are irreconcilable.

384
00:27:36,084 --> 00:27:38,421
Then how'd she see
the reflection in the door?

385
00:27:38,488 --> 00:27:39,589
She couldn't have.

386
00:27:39,655 --> 00:27:41,957
But she did.

387
00:27:42,023 --> 00:27:46,429
Sometimes we misconceive certain
events to a particular element

388
00:27:46,496 --> 00:27:47,896
and are mistaken.

389
00:27:49,766 --> 00:27:50,899
Her eyes are gone.

390
00:27:52,368 --> 00:27:53,469
She did not see.

391
00:27:53,536 --> 00:27:57,707
Oh, this is inhumane.

392
00:27:57,774 --> 00:27:59,442
You heard the doctor,

393
00:28:00,376 --> 00:28:02,879
blind as a bat.

394
00:28:02,944 --> 00:28:06,948
Putting her through
all these needless experiments

395
00:28:07,015 --> 00:28:09,886
as if she was a guinea pig...

396
00:28:09,951 --> 00:28:14,990
Just have some decency
and put her out of her misery.

397
00:28:16,259 --> 00:28:17,560
[sighs]

398
00:28:20,128 --> 00:28:21,798
What's everybody
looking at me for?

399
00:28:21,864 --> 00:28:23,499
What are you saying?

400
00:28:23,566 --> 00:28:24,734
You know what I'm saying.

401
00:28:24,801 --> 00:28:26,803
Because I've said it before.

402
00:28:26,869 --> 00:28:30,840
Have some decency
and put her out of her misery.

403
00:28:30,907 --> 00:28:32,508
Have compassion.

404
00:28:32,575 --> 00:28:35,344
I'm going to give you
five seconds of compassion

405
00:28:35,411 --> 00:28:38,414
before I do something
that I won't regret.

406
00:28:38,481 --> 00:28:40,683
[gasping]

407
00:28:43,619 --> 00:28:45,421
Did you just hear what he said?

408
00:28:47,989 --> 00:28:51,160
Oh, my God, are you going to
let him talk to me like this?

409
00:28:51,227 --> 00:28:53,496
- Yes.
- [scoffs]

410
00:28:55,932 --> 00:28:57,200
[sighs]

411
00:28:58,267 --> 00:28:59,302
Assholes.

412
00:29:00,303 --> 00:29:01,437
Good riddance.

413
00:29:04,640 --> 00:29:06,476
Thank you
for all the melodrama.

414
00:29:07,844 --> 00:29:09,345
I'd like to go to sleep now.

415
00:29:19,789 --> 00:29:21,122
I would have slugged her.

416
00:29:23,759 --> 00:29:30,666
[Lily] "As... for... the... end,

417
00:29:31,868 --> 00:29:36,906
but... then... because."

418
00:29:40,510 --> 00:29:43,179
"Your hands read for you."

419
00:29:45,781 --> 00:29:50,286
"Letters to ponder

420
00:29:50,353 --> 00:29:54,257
messages from yonder."

421
00:29:54,323 --> 00:29:57,760
[frightful music]

422
00:29:57,827 --> 00:29:59,027
[disembodied voice] Hi, Lily.

423
00:30:00,363 --> 00:30:02,865
Stay away from the window.

424
00:30:05,635 --> 00:30:07,336
[panting]

425
00:30:14,343 --> 00:30:17,013
The doctor gave me
some medicine

426
00:30:17,078 --> 00:30:20,115
to dilate the pupils
and calm the nerves.

427
00:30:20,182 --> 00:30:22,083
[suspenseful music]

428
00:30:45,007 --> 00:30:46,776
We may hand it off to the feds.

429
00:30:47,843 --> 00:30:49,211
Tell me something new.

430
00:30:49,278 --> 00:30:51,347
Well, no more miracles
till I get paid.

431
00:30:51,414 --> 00:30:54,450
[sighs] Okay, green on the way.

432
00:30:54,517 --> 00:30:56,586
- Asshole.
- [helicopter whirring]

433
00:30:59,455 --> 00:31:01,157
Miracle if he gets paid.

434
00:31:01,223 --> 00:31:03,091
[dramatic music]

435
00:33:02,812 --> 00:33:04,213
[chittering]

436
00:33:12,488 --> 00:33:16,092
Shh, squirrel, be careful.

437
00:33:16,159 --> 00:33:18,728
Your trees are being used
to hide someone watching me.

438
00:33:20,062 --> 00:33:21,564
[chittering continues]

439
00:33:47,890 --> 00:33:50,493
Hi, Lily.
Oh, heh, sorry.

440
00:33:50,559 --> 00:33:51,827
I didn't mean to startle you.

441
00:33:51,894 --> 00:33:54,396
- I'm Dick, private eye.
- Oh, yes, hi.

442
00:33:54,463 --> 00:33:57,167
Sorry, my guard was down because
my attention is on there.

443
00:33:57,234 --> 00:34:00,137
Those four trees with the people
standing behind them?

444
00:34:00,203 --> 00:34:02,004
Oh, yes.
How do you know?

445
00:34:02,071 --> 00:34:03,839
I've been following them.

446
00:34:03,906 --> 00:34:04,940
Can I sit?

447
00:34:08,811 --> 00:34:10,279
[grunts]

448
00:34:12,249 --> 00:34:14,517
Would you like a sandwich?

449
00:34:14,583 --> 00:34:15,751
We have an extra?

450
00:34:15,818 --> 00:34:17,586
Yes.
I packed one extra for you.

451
00:34:17,653 --> 00:34:19,355
[bag rustles]

452
00:34:19,421 --> 00:34:21,023
Why?

453
00:34:21,090 --> 00:34:22,858
I know you were joining
my picnic.

454
00:34:24,161 --> 00:34:25,995
Ah. Hmm.

455
00:34:29,064 --> 00:34:30,866
Peanut butter and banana. Huh!

456
00:34:30,933 --> 00:34:31,867
My favorite.

457
00:34:31,934 --> 00:34:34,204
Yes, I know.

458
00:34:34,271 --> 00:34:39,041
Lily, do you have any suspicion on
why anybody would want to hurt you?

459
00:34:39,108 --> 00:34:40,776
Kill me dead?

460
00:34:40,843 --> 00:34:43,078
I'm a little fuzzy on that one.

461
00:34:43,146 --> 00:34:46,448
Uncle Fun I know
since I'm a little girl.

462
00:34:46,515 --> 00:34:48,551
I can never believe he would
hurt me.

463
00:34:48,617 --> 00:34:50,920
Aunt Jane, she's just timid
and nice.

464
00:34:50,986 --> 00:34:54,557
She couldn't hurt a fly.
Aunt Naggie, whatever.

465
00:34:54,623 --> 00:34:57,393
She's just a sour puss
and her own worst enemy.

466
00:34:57,459 --> 00:34:59,528
What about, um, Amber?

467
00:34:59,595 --> 00:35:03,233
No, blood sister.
Any blood shed by me would be bled by her.

468
00:35:03,300 --> 00:35:05,034
Lily, if it's okay with you, um,

469
00:35:05,100 --> 00:35:07,570
I'm going to keep an eye on you
until I discover the murderer...

470
00:35:07,636 --> 00:35:09,805
- Ah.
- ...before you're murdered.

471
00:35:09,872 --> 00:35:11,208
Yes, better that way.

472
00:35:13,143 --> 00:35:14,643
You have a nice face.

473
00:35:15,778 --> 00:35:16,846
How would you know?

474
00:35:17,980 --> 00:35:19,014
I feel it.

475
00:35:20,883 --> 00:35:21,917
May I?

476
00:35:23,352 --> 00:35:25,188
[soft music]

477
00:35:27,990 --> 00:35:29,925
- I knew it.
- [chuckles]

478
00:35:29,992 --> 00:35:33,230
Yeah, well, I was...
I was hammered in the ring a little bit.

479
00:35:33,296 --> 00:35:36,599
You know, I got the cauliflower
ears, crooked nose, messed-up teeth.

480
00:35:36,665 --> 00:35:40,237
- [both chuckle]
- Not what I'm feeling. Maybe your alter-ego.

481
00:35:40,303 --> 00:35:43,240
- [chuckles]
- How much would you cost?

482
00:35:44,673 --> 00:35:46,243
[sighs] I wouldn't charge you.

483
00:35:47,177 --> 00:35:48,644
Why?

484
00:35:48,711 --> 00:35:50,846
Well, in order for me
to be my best,

485
00:35:50,913 --> 00:35:54,284
my heart's got to be into it,
so no money.

486
00:35:54,351 --> 00:35:55,618
You do this often?

487
00:35:55,684 --> 00:35:57,254
Ah, it's my first one.

488
00:35:57,320 --> 00:35:58,520
So why now?

489
00:35:59,555 --> 00:36:00,890
Time to be my best.

490
00:36:02,925 --> 00:36:05,961
Okay, you can work for free
and kill my murderer.

491
00:36:06,028 --> 00:36:08,164
And then I pay you
with my inheritance.

492
00:36:08,231 --> 00:36:10,799
- Fair? Deal?
- [chuckles] Okay, we'll see.

493
00:36:10,866 --> 00:36:13,203
Okay, let's go.
Them trees are too busy for me.

494
00:36:14,036 --> 00:36:15,238
All right.

495
00:36:31,887 --> 00:36:33,789
[suspenseful music]

496
00:36:42,564 --> 00:36:43,999
You killed her?

497
00:36:44,900 --> 00:36:46,468
Not yet.

498
00:36:46,535 --> 00:36:49,672
So this retainer
is premeditated.

499
00:36:49,738 --> 00:36:52,508
- [Naggie] Yes.
- Let's do this another way.

500
00:36:52,574 --> 00:36:55,778
After the crime, then you pay me
to represent you.

501
00:36:58,747 --> 00:36:59,782
Mm-hmm.

502
00:37:03,585 --> 00:37:05,255
Uh, you're forgetting
your money.

503
00:37:06,055 --> 00:37:08,557
No, I'm not.

504
00:37:08,624 --> 00:37:10,592
I don't do business this way.

505
00:37:12,461 --> 00:37:13,862
After the murder,

506
00:37:13,929 --> 00:37:18,867
you get me off scot-free
and you get 10%.

507
00:37:18,934 --> 00:37:20,035
Of what?

508
00:37:21,637 --> 00:37:24,140
Hmm. [chuckles] You know.

509
00:37:26,608 --> 00:37:27,843
[sighs]

510
00:37:30,479 --> 00:37:32,315
[Naggie laughs]

511
00:37:33,183 --> 00:37:35,050
[phone rings]

512
00:37:35,117 --> 00:37:36,719
[upbeat music]

513
00:37:36,785 --> 00:37:38,554
Johnny Jerkoff.

514
00:37:38,620 --> 00:37:40,256
Where are you?

515
00:37:40,323 --> 00:37:42,691
I am on fire.

516
00:37:42,758 --> 00:37:44,260
Keep playing, pumpkins.

517
00:37:44,327 --> 00:37:45,561
I'm coming.

518
00:37:45,627 --> 00:37:50,065
I can't tell you how many times
I've...

